<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Begins Vacation in Valdai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
Sunday arrived in Valdai area, northwestern Russian, to spend his
two-week vacation, the Interfax news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin is likely to enjoy fishing in the Valdai town which is
located on the bank of the Valdai lake.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's residence is on the bank of lake Uzhin, one in the
chain of nearly 100 lakes.
</P>
<P>
The Russian president caught a cold at the end of last year and
took a rest at Barvikha outside Moscow for two weeks.
</P>
<P>
He returned to the Kremlin on December 23, 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
