<HEADLINE> 2nd Black Box of Crashed Flight MI185 Recovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The second black box, or the
cockpit voice recorder, of the crashed SilkAir flight MI185 was
finally recovered from the Musi River near Palembang, Indonesia,
late on Sunday after 17 days' of painstaking search operation, the
Singapore television said.
</P>
<P>
SilkAir flight MI185 crashed into the Musi River, near
Palembang, Indonesia, on December 19, with 97 passengers and seven
crew members on board. No survivors were found after the mishap
took place.
</P>
<P>
The first black box, the flight data recorder, was found in the
river on December 27, nine days after the crash and it was taken
to Washington's National Transport Safety Bureau for tests and
further investigations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
