<HEADLINE> China Takes Measures to Alleviate Burdens on Enterprises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Finance
today issued a notice on the abolition of 29 administrative
fees on Chinese enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The move is expected to reduce burdens on enterprises by over
300 million yuan annually, ministry sources said.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the decision was made in line with the spirit
of related decisions by the Chinese Communist Party Central
Committee and the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The 29 administrative fees are directly related to the private
enterprises, motor vehicle trade market and motor vehicle
maintenance industries.
</P>
<P>
The notice instructs the financial and pricing departments in
China to strictly carry out the provisions listed therein.
</P>
</TEXT>
