<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockets Keep Lead in Chinese Basketball League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Defending champions August First
Rockets kept their lead in the Chinese first division basketball
league from the season most scoring game in the 12th round on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Rockets won in the road 110-63 over the struggling Zhejiang
Squarrels thanks for illustratious performance of Wang Zhizhi and
Linan, both in the national squad.
</P>
<P>
But American Mike King pulled back for the Squarrels to shorten
the gap to 10 points midway in the first half before the
star-stunned Rockets pulled away to finish the half with 54-30.
</P>
<P>
With the start center Yu Leping absence for injury, Squarrels
surrendered the inside to Wang, who is the best and most potential
center in China.
</P>
<P>
The Shandong Flaming Bulls were still in the touch with a
well-deserved 69-56 win over Beijing Ducks, trailing the Rockets
with one point on the standings.
</P>
<P>
The Ducks played a turnover-plagued game in Jinan, Shandong
province, while the home team steered from a 14-all tie to lead
all the way to the final victory.
</P>
<P>
Playing with double-center tactics for both, Flaming Bulls
proved more steady on Ji Minshang and Gong Xiaobin after Ba Teer
was benched for four fouls earlier in the second half, leaving
teammate Shan Tao struggling in the inside in vain.
</P>
<P>
No surprise sparked in the debuts in a new year of the national
top basketball league as all the winning teams underlined the
second stage with their superiority over rivals in the first round.
</P>
<P>
All the hosts lose their advantage of the local partisans and
arenas except for Shandong, seeing Jinan Army Pegasus beaten by
Liaoning Hunters 60-57, Sichuan Pandas trounced by Guangdong
Tigers 81-72, Shenyang Lions overpowered by Jiangsu Dragons 80-65,
and Lianhang Eagles edged by Shanghai Sharks 72-62. 
</P>
</TEXT>
