<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia's UNIP Condemns Continued Detention of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Zambia's largest opposition
party, the United National Independence Party (UNIP), today
condemned the continued detention of its leader and former
president Kenneth Kaunda.
</P>
<P>
At a news briefing at UNIP's headquarters at the Freedom House
here, UNIP National Chairman General Malimba Masheke told
journalists and more than one hundred party cadres that his party
"strongly condemns the continued and unjustified detention of Dr.
Kaunda."
</P>
<P>
He said shifting Kaunda from prison to house arrest has not
improved Kaunda's conditions and that Kaunda's house has been
turned into a prison because the former president is not free to
see his family members or to communicate with the party members.
</P>
<P>
The government wanted to associate Kaunda with the abortive
military coup and tried to make the nation believe that he is
involved in the coup attempt so as to justify his detention, said
Masheke.
</P>
<P>
It is "intolerable and unacceptable" to imprison an "innocent"
person, said the UNIP national chairman.
</P>
<P>
As for the on-going state of emergency, Masheke said that the
ruling Movement for Multi-Party Democracy (MMD) and its political
leaders as well as the police take advantage of the state of
emergency to "settle old scores and neutralize the opposition".
</P>
<P>
UNIP called on the government to lift the state of emergency
and stop using it to "harass" the opposition and the media,
Masheke stated.
</P>
<P>
Kaunda was arrested last December for alleged involvement in
the country's coup attempt and was later shifted to house arrest.
Earlier reports said that Kaunda's party has threatened to send
the "old man" back to prison because of his present "worse"
conditions.
</P>
<P>
Besides the 73 year-old former president, 90 people have been
detained under the state of emergency declared by President
Frederick Chiluba following the October coup which aimed to
topple the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
