<HEADLINE> Canada Issues New Coin to Mark Chinese New Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Royal Canadian Mint is
marking the Chinese New Year with a new series of coins.
</P>
<P>
On Saturday, the mint unveiled in Toronto and Vancouver a
15-dollar (10.5 USD) coin featuring a tiger, marking the Chinese
lunar Year of Tiger, which begins January 28.
</P>
<P>
"It's the first time the Royal Canadian Mint has done anything
for the Asian-Canadian market," a mint spokesperson was quoted as
saying by reports today.
</P>
<P>
The new coin is sterling silver with a 24-karat gold cameo of a
tiger in the centre.
</P>
<P>
It is the first in a 12-coin series based on the symbols of the
Chinese lunar calendar.
</P>
<P>
The mint, which is producing a total of 68,888 of the coins, is
offering them for 68.88 dollars each, along with a collector's
box. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
