<HEADLINE> U.S. Chemical Warehouse Fire Force 3000 to Flee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 4 (Xinhua) -- More than 3,000 people were
evacuated from both sides of the Ohio River earlier Sunday after
fire engulfed a warehouse that stores potentially explosive
chemicals, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
A Cargill company center caught fire at about 2:30 a.m. Sunday
and its store of pesticides, herbicides and fertilizers, such as
ammonium nitrate and 24D, threatened communities from Maysville,
Kentucky, and those across the the Ohio River in Ohio.
</P>
<P>
At about 2:45 a.m., police, fire, ambulance and local
Department of Emergency Services workers began to rouse the
residents around the warehouse out by loudspeakers.
</P>
<P>
The fire had consumed about 85 percent of the building
and the deadly fumes should dissipate in the extremely high
temperature, officials said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
