<HEADLINE> Earthquake Strikes Loyalty Islands in S. Pacific </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 4 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake with a
preliminary magnitude of 7.0 struck the Loyalty Islands in the
South Pacific earlier today, the United Press International
reported.
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted a U.S. Geological Survey spokeswoman as
saying that the quake occurred at 1.12 a.m. EST (0612 GMT). The
epicenter of the quake was located at 22 degrees south latitude,
171 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
The Pacific Tsunami Warning Center has issued a tsunami warning
for all areas of the Pacific Basin except California, Oregon,
Washington, British Columbia and Alaska.
</P>
<P>
The Loyalty Islands lie in the Coral Sea northwest of New
Zealand and west of Australia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
