<HEADLINE> Visit of Syrian Vice President to France Delayed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 4 (Xinhua) -- A visit by the Vice President of
Syria Abdel Halim Khaddam to France was delayed on Sunday due to
the stormy Weather which hit France, Agence France-Presse (AFP)
quoted official sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam, to be accompanied by Syrian Foreign Minister Farouk
al-Shareh, was originally scheduled to arrive here Sunday for a
two-day visit, during which he will talk with President Jacques
Chirac and Prime Minister Lionel Jospin the latest development of
the situation in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
The Elysee presidential palace announced Sunday that Chirac
will meet with Khaddam on Tuesday morning.
</P>
<P>
The visit by Khaddam coincided with an Israeli announcement
that it would accept the United Nations Security Council
resolution calling for its withdrawal from southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
But Israel said Lebanon must ensure the security of its
northern border, which repeatedly came under rocket attacks by the
Hezbollah guerrillas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
