<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Traffic Accident in France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Four young people were killed and
eight injured Saturday night in a violent chain crash of vehicles
on a highway in Saint-Marcel-de-Felines in Loire, central France,
reported Agence France-Presse Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Three of the victims, two brothers and a girl friend of one of
theirs who were aged from 16 to 25, were burnt in their Peugeot
205 car, while the fourth, a 19-year-old belonging to the same
family, were thrown out of the car and died later in hospital
because of heart and breath problems.
</P>
<P>
Police said that the accident took place after the drivers in
the Peugeot 205 lost control and hit another car driving in the
opposite direction.
</P>
<P>
About 800 people are killed in traffic accidents each month in
France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
