<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over $50 Million to be Invested in Oil Tapping in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique will invest 50-75
million U.S. Dollars in exploring oil and natural gas this year,
the Mozambique Information Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Arsenio Mabote, director of national coal
and hydrocarbon with the Ministry of Mining and Energy, who said
several foreign companies are tapping petroleum and gas in the
country.
</P>
<P>
He said foreign companies are willing to invest in Mozambique
for oil and gas exploration mainly because of its political
stability and prospecting incentives. 
</P>
