<HEADLINE> Nagano Winter Olympics Receive 71 Entry Forms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 5 (Xinhua) -- A total of 71 countries and
regions have submitted entry forms to take part in next month's
Nagano Winter Olympics, organisers said in Nagano on Monday.
</P>
<P>
It would make the Games the biggest in terms of the number of
participating countries and regions if all of them send athletes
after qualifying the standards set by international winter sports
federations.
</P>
<P>
A record 67 countries took part in the last Winter Olympics in
Lillehammer, Norway, in 1994.
</P>
<P>
The Nagano Games will also be the biggest in terms of the
program -- 68 sports including three new events like women's ice
hockey, curling and snowboarding.
</P>
<P>
Kenya, Mongolia and Portugal have recently asked for the
qualifications of their athletes approved for the Games which were
held from February 7 to 22, the Nagano Olympic Organising
Committee (NAOC) said.
</P>
<P>
Final confirmation of the number of countries would be made
after January 26 when national Olympic committees submit the names
of the athletes they plan to field.
</P>
<P>
A total of 82 committees initially accepted invitations to take
part in the 18th Winter Olympics, the second to be held in Asia
after the 1972 Games in another Japanese city -- Sapporo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
