<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Sees Ski Industry Booming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- People are swarming into ski rinks
in Bulgaria, making this season the best for the country's ski
industry after years of recession.
</P>
<P>
Pamporovo, one of the biggest ski resorts in Bulgaria, reported
having received over 10 thousand skiing fans each day since
January 1, the highest record in nearly a decade.
</P>
<P>
As a result, restaurants and hotels around the ski resort are
packed with tourists who, as in the past, are mostly from other
countries. But the number of Bulgarians there is also on the rise.
</P>
<P>
Tourism in winter, an important revenue source for the ski
industry, is known as "white business" in Bulgaria, and this time
of the year is just the beginning of the season.
</P>
<P>
However, business was on the decline in past several years.
</P>
<P>
To bring back the business, local authorities late last year
repaired travel and business facilities at ski resorts, and
stepped up oversight on business practices there. 
</P>
</TEXT>
