<HEADLINE> Bomb Alert on Air France Airbus Proved False </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 5 (Xinhua) -- A bomb alert Monday on an Air
France Airbus 340 passenger plane on a flight from Lagos, Nigeria,
to Paris was proved false and the plane took off again mid-day
from Marseille, where it made an emergency landing.
</P>
<P>
Police checked all the luggage on board the passenger plane and
no bomb or sign of explosives were found, reported Agence
France-Presse.
</P>
<P>
The French airport authorities in Paris received an anonymous
call at 04:45 local time, which said that a bomb was placed on the
Airbus.
</P>
<P>
All the passengers were evacuated to a waiting hall of the
airport of Marseille, before the plane was flown to Marignane in
Bouches-du-Rhone near Marseille for checking. 
