<HEADLINE> Pak Prime Minister Vows to Address Social Ills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif said here Monday that his government would set up
committees to address social ills such as corruption and
injustice.
</P>
<P>
"The country cannot make progress when social evils like
corruption, injustice, inequality and dishonesty continue to deny
people their right to progress," Sharif said while addressing a
meeting of the General Council of the Pakistan Muslim League
(PML-N), according to the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was attended by more than 700 delegates from all
over the country.
</P>
<P>
Sharif said the committees will on the one hand evaluate the
government's performance and on the other set the pace for durable
progress based on justice and equality.
</P>
<P>
Members of the committees will be people with genuine desire to
serve the nation, he added.
</P>
<P>
Referring to police excesses, Sharif said, "We want to remove
demerits from the system so that the deserving and the qualified
come forward and serve the nation."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the committees would look into complaints against
the police as well as the services of government departments.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Sharif expressed his confidence that PML-N workers
would lend their fullest cooperation in materializing the plans
undertaken by the government.  
