<HEADLINE> East China Province Using WB Loans to Develop Basic Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, January 5 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province has
used 840 million US dollars of loans from the World Bank to
develop its basic industries.
</P>
<P>
The province has so far signed contracts to introduce more than
one billion US dollars of WB's loans for 33 projects.
</P>
<P>
Most of the WB-funded projects are related to the leading
industrial and infrastructure sectors.
</P>
<P>
The expressway from the provincial capital of Jinan to the
coastal city of Qingdao has been built with a loan of 110 million
US dollars of the WB and has a daily handling capacity of 40,000
vehicles.
</P>
<P>
The expressway has greatly boosted the economic development
along its way, bringing in five billion yuan in economic returns
to the local people annually.
</P>
<P>
The introduction of 310 million US dollars of WB's loans has
helped the Zouxian County Power Plant increase its annual power
output by 7.8 billion KWh, thus greatly easing power shortages in
the province.
</P>
<P>
WB's loans have also been used on the development of local
agriculture, animal husbandry, tidal zones and aquiculture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
