<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hebei Improves Social Welfare Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, January 5 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province has accelerated social welfare reform by setting up and
improving five welfare service networks.
</P>
<P>
The five networks offer assistance to the disabled, disaster
and poverty relief, and services for the dependents of soldiers and
the elderly, as well as wedding and funeral arrangements.
</P>
<P>
The province has opened more than 2,400 welfare enterprises
staffed by over 750,000 workers, including 33,530 disabled people.
</P>
<P>
The province's disaster, poverty relief, reserve funds and
grain supply departments have helped some 3.5 million impoverished
families to become well-to-do.
</P>
<P>
In addition, homes for the elderly have been established in all
towns and villages, with 32 welfare centers across the province
housing more than 8,400 people.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province has designated 166 glorious families
for dependents of soldiers, and 140 homes for retired army
officers.  
</P>
