<HEADLINE> Bonn Calls for Curbing Influx of Kurdish Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Germany Monday reiterated its call
on its European partners, especially Italy, to tighten border
controls to prevent a mass influx of Kurdish refugees from Turkey
to Europe.
</P>
<P>
Describing the situation as "threatening", German Interior
Minister Manfred Kanther insisted that Italy and Greece should
take considerably tougher measures against illegal immigration.
</P>
<P>
Kanther made the remarks after an influx of would-be
immigrants, most of them Kurds, have reached Italy's coast from
Turkey during the past few weeks. More ships carrying thousands of
Kurds are reportedly en route.
</P>
<P>
Fearing that many of the Kurds would finally head for Germany,
which has a large Kurdish population and a more liberal asylum
policy, Kanther said that Germany has already reinforced police
forces at its southern border and would send back those immigrants
who slipped illegally into Germany. 
</P>
