<HEADLINE> 36 People Die in Bus Accident in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 5 (Xinhua) -- A total of 36 Zimbabweans died
on the spot and 40 were critically injured this morning after
their bus veered off the road and rammed into a cold room at the
19 kilometre peg along the Nyanga-Nyamaropa road in east
Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Inspector Lameck Jena, officer-in-charge of Nyanga police
station, said the accident occurred around 06:30 am when the bus
with 77 passengers on board, was travelling from Nyanga to
Harare.
</P>
<P>
This is the second time in seven years that buses from the
same company have been involved in major accidents along the same
road.
</P>
<P>
In 1991 a bus belonging to B and C Bus Company overturned
along the Nyanga to Nyamaropa road and killed 89 school children
and teachers from Regina Coeli Mission in Nyanga, Jena said.
</P>
