<HEADLINE> Zimbabwean Stockmarket Indexes Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean stockmarket, the
second largest one in Africa, opened the year more active with
the key industrial index gaining a massive 326 points to close at
7,522 today.
</P>
<P>
The market which plunged dramatically in the last quarter of
last year continued with its recovery on the back of rising share
prices in a number of counters.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the rains that have been lashing some parts of
the country in the past few days coupled with the disbursement by
the world bank of one billion Zimbabwe dollars (60 million U.S.
dollars) in balance of payments support last December appear to
be lifting investor confidence.
</P>
<P>
"Investors are coming back from the holidays and taking
advantage of the value that has been created in the market in the
last few weeks," said an analyst with quincor stockbrokers.
</P>
<P>
However, the industrial index is still 1,263 points down
compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The mining index today rose 10 points to close at 469.
</P>
