<HEADLINE> Increasing Number of Telephone Subscribers In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Latest statistics shows that the
number of telephone subscribers in China has hit 83.6 million,
including the newly-added 22 million users in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The number of mobile telephone subscribers, with 6.4 million
added last year, has reached 13.25 million, ranking China in the
third place in the world, according to an official of the Ministry
of Post and Telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
China spent only six years increasing its mobile phone users
from 18,000 in 1990 to 3.63 million in 1995, and the number
finally exceeded 10 million in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Experts predict that China will have the world's biggest number
of mobile phone subscribers in the next decade, Guangming Daily, a
leading Chinese newspaper, reported today.  
</P>
