<HEADLINE> Top Chinese, Iraqi Legislators Meet in Beijing  (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC), met here today with a delegation from the Iraqi National
Assembly led by Speaker Saadoun Hammadi.
</P>
<P>
Extending a warm welcome to the Iraqi guests, Qiao said it is
the Iraqi speaker's third visit to China, and that Hammadi has
made many contributions to the enhancement of bilateral contacts
and friendly ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the ongoing visit would serve to
further advance the bilateral relations between the two nations.
</P>
<P>
Qiao noted that the bilateral relations between the two nations
are very good on a long run, and that the Chinese NPC is ready to
develop friendly ties with the Iraqi National Assembly, in a hope
that both sides will increase mutual understanding, contacts and
cooperation by means of exchanges.
</P>
<P>
China holds that international conflicts should be settled
peacefully and it opposes the use of force or the threat of force,
Qiao said, adding that China also stands that all countries, big
or small, rich or poor, and strong or weak, are equal members of
the international community.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that major issues of the world should be
resettled by various countries through equal consultations on the
basis of mutual respect.
</P>
<P>
"We are ready to play a positive role in the United Nations and
set forth proposals in the interests of the world and all the
people," the top Chinese legislator said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, China stands for peaceful settlement of the
state-to-state and regional conflicts in accordance with the UN
Charter and the international norms, and for a fair and reasonable
solution as early as possible to the issues left over by the Gulf
War, including the sanctions against Iraq, on the basis of the
relevant UN Security Council resolutions.
</P>
</TEXT>
