<HEADLINE> Chinese Railway Sector Enhances Overseas Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 5 (Xinhua) -- China's railway sector has
consolidated its cooperation with overseas, by investing 170
million US dollars of foreign funds to purchase machinery and
equipment in 1997.
</P>
<P>
Foreign trade of the sector reached 416 million US dollars in
the year, and the turnover of overseas contractual projects, labor
cooperation and design and consultancy topped 400 million US
dollars, up 62 and 76 percent, respectively, from 1996.
</P>
<P>
Work was accelerated on the renovation project for a 3,000-plus
km of outdated railway in Nigeria, China's largest ever contracted
overseas railway cooperation project, to ensure that it be
completed in June of this year.
</P>
<P>
Trains carried 1.77 million passengers and 9.4 million tons of
cargo on China's international railway lines last year, increasing
14 and 7 percent, respectively, over 1996.
</P>
<P>
Beijing-HK and Shanghai-HK fast trains also opened last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
