<HEADLINE> Nowen Wins World Cup Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Ylva Nowen took a women's
Alpine skiing World Cup slalom in Bormio on Monday for her fourth
successive win of the season.
</P>
<P>
The Swede won in a combined time of one minute 27.81 seconds
after Urska Hrovat of Slovenia crashed out on the second leg.
</P>
<P>
The two had been tied after the first run and were also level
at the first split time of the second with Hrovat following Nowen
down the course.
</P>
<P>
Germany's Hilde Gerg, who finished the first leg in 13th
place, was second in 1:28.53 after making several mistakes on
the top part of the piste. Slovenia's Spela Pretnar was third in
1:28.58.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Deborah Compagnoni, the double Olympic champion and
local favourite, finished in 12th place. 
