<TEXT>
<P>
SHANTOU, January 5 (Xinhua) -- High and new-tech industries in
Shantou city of south China's Guangdong Province, one of the
country's five special economic zones approved in the early 1980s,
have emerged as the city's newest economic growth area.
</P>
<P>
Over the past three years, the city has imported nearly 600
projects for new products, materials, and technologies, which
yielded more than 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion US dollars) in
output value, according to Zhang Yingqiang, director of the city
Science and Technology Commission.
</P>
<P>
Progress in science and technology now contributes 40.6 percent
to the city's economic development, and is still gaining more
shares.
</P>
<P>
Twenty of the city's enterprises have been listed by Guangdong
Province as high-tech ones, two of which have already been
approved by the State Science and Technology Commission as major
high-tech enterprise groups.
</P>
<P>
In addition, some high-tech enterprises have passed the
internationally recognized quality certification ISO9000. The
Shantou Supersonic Apparatus Research Institute, for example, has
developed more than 40 high-tech products, which are doing well
both at home and overseas market.  
</P>
