<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Peso Falls to New Record Low </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine currency, the
peso, fell by about 4 percent to a new record low of 42.65 pesos
against the U.S. dollar on Monday, dealers said.
</P>
<P>
The peso closed at an average of 41.738 pesos per U.S. dollar
on a turnover volume of 17.5 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said falls in other Southeast Asian currencies,
especially the Indonesian rupiah, and heavy corporate demand for
dollars quickly pushed the peso down to the new all-time low.
</P>
<P>
The peso plunged to the new level in the first 90 minutes of
trading, forcing a halt to all transactions beyond that level for
the rest of the day.
</P>
<P>
The peso has devaluated by some 61 percent since the financial
storm began to sweep Southeast Asia in July last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
