<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Heart Patients Implanted With New Device </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Experts at the All India
Institute of Medical Sciences (AIIMS) here have successfully
carried out the implantation of a new mechanical device to assist
patients with severely impaired hearts, the Press Trust of India
(PTI) said Monday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time in Asia that such a new device has been
implanted through operations on four Indian patients, the PTI
quoted AIIMS Dr. P. Venugopal as saying.
</P>
<P>
The device, manufactured by a U.S. company, aids the heart in
pumping blood to the conduits of the body, thereby reducing stress
and workload on a patient's heart after surgery. It allows
patients a near-normal lifestyle after the operation, he said.
</P>
<P>
"Heart mate is a boon for those patients with long-standing
heart ailment awaiting a suitable donor. The use of this device
offers a better survival by acting as a support device during the
waiting period. Almost 80 percent of patients who registered for
transplant at the AIIMS have already died for want of a suitable
heart," he said.
</P>
<P>
The device, which has a life span of maximum two years, is less
cumbersome compared to previous devices and the patients can be
discharged within two weeks.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
