<HEADLINE> South Koreans Dominate Junior Speedskating Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Lee Seung-Jae of South Korea
won two titles in men's events at the World Junior Short Track
Speedskating Championships in St Louis on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Lee claimed the golds in the 1,000 meters with a time of one
minute 32.33 seconds and the Super 1,500 meters in two hours 24
minutes 93 seconds, edging Francois-Louis Tremblay of Canada to
second in both races.
</P>
<P>
Both men finished the two-day competition with 11
points. Tremblay had five points while Lee had only one before
Sunday's final.
</P>
<P>
Joo Min-Jin won the women's championship over compatriot Kim
Jung-Moon with a total 16 points, ahead of Kim's 12 and
third-place finisher Kristina Vuteva of Bulgaria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
