<HEADLINE> Japanese Shirahata Sets World Record for All-Around </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Keiji Shirahata of Japan
registered a world record of the men's all-around overall points
in capturing his fourth straight national speedskating title on
the Olympic ground in Nagano on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Shirahata collected a total points of four-race in 155.966,
eclipsing the previous mark of 156.201 points set by Dutchman
Rintje Ritsma four years ago.
</P>
<P>
The overall points world record is based on race times in all
four distances, as in 500, 1,500, 5,000 and 10,000 meters for
men's event.  
</P>
</TEXT>
