<HEADLINE> China's Foreign Ministry Commments on Taiwanese Singapore Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 5 (Xinhua) -- China today said it hopes that
Singapore will stick to a "one China" policy and will not do
something that harms bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
The comment comes from Foreign Ministry spokesman Shen Guofang,
who was asked to comment on the recent visit of Taiwan's
"vice-president" Lien Chan to Singapore and his meetings with
Singaporean leaders.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government firmly opposes the "two Chinas" or "one
China, one Taiwan" policies, and opposes the practice of any
country that has diplomatic ties with China of having any form
of official relations or contacts with Taiwan, Shen said. The
government's position on this is consistent and clear-cut, firm,
and is respected by the majority of the world's countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
The government of the People's Republic of China is recognized
as the sole legitimate government representing the whole people of
China, and Taiwan is an inalienable part of that, he pointed out.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
