<HEADLINE> All Zambian Parties Urged to Take Dialog </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The National Patriotic Alliance
(NPA) grouping 12 opposition parties has appealed all Zambian
political parties to the inter-party talks to put national
interests above individual party.
</P>
<P>
Times of Zambia today quoted NPA acting chairman Chibeza Mfuni
as saying on Sunday that the umbrella alliance remains firmly
committed to serious dialog and maintains that everything
possible should be done by all to revive the inter-party talks,
which have postponed to late this month from early this month
after a number of opposition parties including the NPA announced
their withdrawal of the talks in protest against the arrest of
former president Kenneth Kaunda.
</P>
<P>
MFUNI said NPA leaders resolve that the inter-party talks to
be attended by party presidents has failed and another round of
secretaries meeting should be held to address and resolve
preliminary issues.
</P>
<P>
He said the preliminary issues have been communicated to the
government, which include lifting the state of emergency, releasing
political detainees and security guarantee for the party leaders to
the talkks.
</P>
<P>
"The presidents' meeting must be taken very seriously and not
in a confrontational approach. this meeting should be about
handshaking in a reassuring atmosphere," he said.
</P>
<P>
At an earlier briefing Malimba Masheke, chairman of the United
National Independence Party (UNIP) led by Kaunda, said UNIP, one
member of the NPA, is willing to participate in any "meaningful"
inter-party talks when Kaunda is freed.
</P>
<P>
Masheke called for an urgent national dialogue under a neutral
convenor to accommodate all stakeholders including churches,
non-government orgazinations (ngo) and civil societies.
</P>
<P>
But Micheal Sata, national secretary of the ruling Movement
for Multi-Party Democracy (MMD), rejected NPA and UNIP's
pre-conditions.
</P>
<P>
Kaunda was arrested on 25 in alleged connection with the
October 28 foiled coup and transferred from prison to house
arrest on 31 of last month.
</P>
<P>
At the preliminary meeting attended by party secretaries early
last month an agenda was worked out for the inter-party talks.
However, after Kaunda's arrest the planned talks were plunged
into stalemate. 
</P>
