<DATE_TIME> 1998-01-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Five SEZs Thriving (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Xiamen became a pilot area with direct air and shipping
services to Taiwan last year, and now has major transport lines to
Japan, Singapore, the Republic of Korea, the US, and the
Mediterranean.
</P>
<P>
Exports amounted to 3.52 billion US dollars and imports,
2.89 billion US dollars, both up 13.6 percent from the previous
year.
</P>
<P>
State-owned enterprises in Xiamen had exports worth 1.64
billion US dollars in the first ten months of 1997, up 23.6
percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Hainan had healthy economic development last year, with
economic growth estimated at 6.7 percent last year, up 1.9
percentage points from the previous year, and industries at or
abov the township level are expected to have sales of 23 billion
yuan, up 16 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Hainan had 7.9 million tourists last year and revenues of 5.5
billion yuan from the industry, up 10.29 percent over the previous
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
