<HEADLINE> Beijing International Exhibition on Water Treatment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 5 (Xinhua) -- China will hold an international
exhibition in Beijing in September in conjunction with an
international symposium on management of water resources and water
treatment technology.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition is a major part of the "China Trans-century
Green Project" and is designed to increase cooperation with the
rest of the world by using more advanced technology, equipment and
management expertise in controlling water pollution and managing
water resources.
</P>
<P>
As part of the exhibition, there will be discussions on
improving the water of China's major river systems.
</P>
<P>
Companies from China, the United States, Japan, Germany,
France, and other countries will be present and will have the
opportunity to hold business negotiations on 100 possible projects
which will import technology and attract funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
