<HEADLINE> African Charged with Drug Trafficking in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, January 5 (Xinhua) -- An Ivory Coast national was
charged in the Magistrate's Court in Jitra, Northern state of
Kedah, Malaysia, Monday, with alleged trafficking in 1.9 kilogram
of heroin.
</P>
<P>
Kovama Koffi Francis, 35, of Glassalle, Ivory Coast, was
alleged to have committed the offense at the Bukit Kayu Hitam
Immigration Complex check point near the Malaysian-Thai border
last Monday morning, the Malaysian national news agency Bernama
reported.
</P>
<P>
He was charged under Section 39B of the Dangerous Drugs Act of
the country, which carries the mandatory death sentence upon
conviction.
</P>
<P>
No plea was recorded, Bernama said.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Senior Registrar Tan Swan Khoh,
sitting as magistrate, postponed the case to March 30 pending
application from Royal Customs and Excise Department's prosecutor
Saidi Ismail to transfer the case to the High Court.  
</P>
</TEXT>
