<HEADLINE> Avalanches Kill Eight in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, January 4 (Xinhua) -- At least eight people were killed
by three avalanches at the weekend in the Canadian province of
British Columbia (B.C.).
</P>
<P>
The avalanches swept down mountains in southeastern British
Columbia burying recreational skiers and snowmobilers.
</P>
<P>
"There have never been so many deaths in one day among three
groups in three different areas," an official from the Canadian
Avalanche Centre said.
</P>
<P>
The storm has prevented police from recovering the bodies of
five skiers and a search is on for one who was still missing
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
So far this winter, 13 people have been killed by avalanches in
western Canada. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
