<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Some 42 state-owned factories
under the ministries of industry, livestock breeding and fishery,
and commerce will be added to the privatization scheme in Myanmar,
an official information sheet said.
</P>
<P>
The privatization scheme also includes other two livestock
breeding farms and 76 cinemas of the Information Ministry.
</P>
<P>
Since Myanmar announced privatization of 51 state-owned
economic enterprises (SEE) in the first phase in January 1995 in
line with the market-oriented economy, the privatization process
has been underway in various forms including auctioning and
leasing out the SEE or establishing joint ventures with local and
foreign entrepreneurs or operating either under buy-back or
counter-trade system.
</P>
<P>
