<HEADLINE> Shaanxi Steps up Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Shaanxi
Province plans to invest 2.55 billion yuan (300 million US
dollars) to launch a comprehensive pollution control project, the
largest environmental protection project in its history.
</P>
<P>
The funding, including a loan of 156 million US dollars from
the Asian Development Bank, will be used for environmental
improvements in the cities of Xi'an, Xianyang and Tongchuan,
according to China Environmental News.
</P>
<P>
The effort will consist of six sub-projects -- three heat
supply projects; two urban natural gas pipeline projects; and a
dust treatment project for a large cement plant in Tongchuan.
</P>
<P>
Related projects will reduce air pollution, conserve energy,
promote the use of clean fuel, improve environmental management
and continue the move towards energy pricing based on the market.
</P>
<P>
They would also replace 515 obsolete boilers and domestic
furnaces with modern, efficient plants and district heating
systems, substitute the use of natural gas for coal in 130,000
households, and reduce emissions of sulfur dioxide by 37,000 tons
annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
