<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swedish Police Arrest Over 300 Neo-Nazis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Swedish police arrested more
than 300 young neo-Nazis after a rock concert in a suburb north of
Stockholm erupted in violence, the Swedish news agency TT reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners from Germany, the United States, Norway and other
countries were among the 314 arrested in Brottby, about 30
kilometers north of the capital.
</P>
<P>
All detainees were questioned and most were freed by Sunday
morning.
</P>
<P>
But 25 were still held in custody on charges involving racial
hatred and inciting to riot.
</P>
<P>
The concert, started on Saturday evening and turned to violence
when police tried to detain a number of youths for allegedly
creating racial agitation. The concert-goers threw beer bottles
and directed fire extinguishers at police and one policeman was
hurt in the head.
</P>
<P>
The police seized T-shirts bearing the Nazi swastika emblem and
compact discs of "rock vaunting the supremacy of the white race".
</P>
<P>
The arrests constituted one of the most extensive operations
carried out by Stockholm police in recent years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
