<HEADLINE> Montgomerie Wins World Championship of Golf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, January 4 (Xinhua) -- Colin Montgomerie of Scotland
beat U.S. PGA champion Davis Love to win the 3.65 million-dollar
World Championship of Golf in Scottsdale, Arizona of the United
States, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Montgomerie, who won the money title on the PGA European Tour
for the fifth straight year, beat Love 2 up in the 36-hole
final to claim the one million-dollar first prize.
</P>
<P>
Montgomerie was 3-up after 33 holes, but Love birdied the
par-three 16th and Montgomerie bogeyed the par-four 17th before
Love conceded the par-five 18th.
</P>
<P>
Love, who finished third on the 1997 PGA money list, picked up
500,000 dollars.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Open champion Ernie Els of South Africa, who lost to
Montgomerie in Saturday's semi-finals, downed Japan's Hajime
Meshiai 4 and 3 to win the 18-hole consolation match and 350,000
dollars.
</P>
<P>
This weekend's competition capped a year-long,
single-elimination tournament featuring 32 players divided into
four groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
