<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, January 5 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON -- British Foreign Secretary Robin Cook said here Sunday
negotiations between the European Union (EU) and central European
countries which have applied for the membership may be completed
by the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
However, the talks would be more difficult than those which led
to Austria, Sweden and Finland joining the EU in 1995, Cook told
BBC television in an interview. It took three years for the three
countries to complete negotiation on the membership.
</P>
<P>
"Those were prosperous countries, small countries, all of them
net contributors (to the EU budget)," Cook said. (EU-Enlargement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- More than 3,000 people were evacuated from both
sides of the Ohio River earlier Sunday after fire engulfed a
warehouse that stores potentially explosive chemicals, reports
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
A Cargill company center caught fire at about 2:30 a.m. Sunday
and its store of pesticides, herbicides and fertilizers, such as
ammonium nitrate and 24D, threatened communities from Maysville,
Kentucky, and those across the the Ohio River in Ohio.
</P>
<P>
At about 2:45 a.m., police, fire, ambulance and local
Department of Emergency Services workers began to rouse the
residents around the warehouse out by
loudspeakers. (US-Fire-Chemicals)
</P>
<P>
