</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- An earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 7.0
struck the Loyalty Islands in the South Pacific earlier Sunday,
the United Press International reported.
</P>
<P>
The news agency quoted a U.S. Geological Survey spokeswoman as
saying that the quake occurred at 1.12 a.m. EST (0612 GMT). The
epicenter of the quake was located at 22 degrees south latitude,
171 degrees east longitude.
</P>
<P>
The Pacific Tsunami Warning Center has issued a tsunami warning
for all areas of the Pacific Basin except California, Oregon,
Washington, British Columbia and Alaska. (US-Quake)
</P>
