<HEADLINE> Private Sector Thrives in Gannan Prefecture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, January 5 (Xinhua) -- The private sector in Gannan
Prefecture, east China's Jiangsu Province, has developed rapidly
due to the local government's efforts to promote the restructuring
of state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Local private investors, most of whom were formerly involved in
the service sector, have now entered the processing, agriculture
and infrastructure sectors.
</P>
<P>
Numerous local private business people are either operating or
investing in parks, gas stations, thrift shops, power stations,
hospitals and kindergarten.
</P>
<P>
Eighty percent of local state companies have undergone
restructuring and many have been sold to individuals.
</P>
<P>
One out of every 10 local residents in the prefecture are
currently working in the private sector which contributes 26
percent of the local revenue.
</P>
<P>
"We permit private businessmen to engage in any business
allowed by the state," according to a local government
official. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
