<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Retail Industry Booms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, January 5 (Xinhua) -- Shoppers in Shanghai, China's
largest trade and financial center, are finding that shopping is
becoming increasingly convenient.
</P>
<P>
The city is currently home to 800 chain stores and 180
retail outlets which are open 24 hours a day.
</P>
<P>
The city also has dozens of shopping centers and department
stores located in major commercial areas.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai residents have also benefited from the increasingly
tough competition amongst retailers who often offer discounts.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Shanghai's total retail sales
jumped by 10 percent to 134 billion yuan during 1997.
</P>
<P>
The total GDP for the city's commercial sector in the first
eleven months of 1997 stood at 30.6 billion yuan, or 11.34 percent
of the total for the period.  
</P>
