<HEADLINE> AL Concerned over Turkish-Israeli War Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 4 (Xinhua) -- The Arab League today expressed
deep concern over the Turkish-Israeli-U.S. naval exercises in
eastern Mediterranean, describing them as a "threat to regional
security."
</P>
<P>
"The exercises threaten the stability and security of the
region and the efforts towards the building of a stable, just and
comprehensive Mideast peace," the Arab League said in a statement
released today.
</P>
<P>
The league views these war games as a way to pressure Syria and
Iraq and as part of a strategy to mould the political future of
the region, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
"These exercises will undermine neither the Arab support of
Iraqi unity and sovereignty nor the Syrian steadfastness, but
(they) rather will strengthen this steadfastness," it added.
</P>
<P>
The league expressed hope that Turkey would reconsider its
military relationship with Israel, which, it said, fully
contradicts the Charter of the Organization of the Islamic
Conference and the traditional ties between Turkey and the Arab
world.
</P>
<P>
The scheduled Turkish-Israeli-U.S. joint exercises next week
have aroused harsh criticism from the Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Turkey, however, repeatedly said that the exercises were not
targeting any third country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
